<font face="Times New Roman, Times, serif" size="4">The Green alternative to Hillary Clinton</font><br>
<font face="Times New Roman, Times, serif" size="5"><b>Howie Hawkins' antiwar challenge</b></font><p>
<font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2">October 20, 2006 | Page 11</font><p>

<font face="Times New Roman, Times, serif" size="3">HOWIE HAWKINS, the veteran activist and Green Party leader from New York, is running for the U.S. Senate as an alternative to pro-war Democrat Sen. Hillary Rodham Clinton.<p>
Opinion polls show that among independent voters, Hawkins has nearly as much support as Clinton's Republican opponent John Spencer. But the political and media establishments are shutting out the Hawkins campaign. On October 22, Hawkins and his supporters will gather outside the WABC Studios in Manhattan to protest Hawkins' exclusion from that morning's Senate candidates' "debate."<p>

